%N A397400 Array read by ascending antidiagonals: A(n, k) = (-1)^n * Sum_{j=1..n+1} Stirling1(k+j, k+1) * Stirling2(n+1, j).
%H A397400 Paolo Xausa, <a href="/A397400/b397400.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..11324</a> (first 150 antidiagonals, flattened).
%H A397400 Max Alekseyev, <a href="https://mathoverflow.net/a/512557">Simplified sum with Stirling numbers of both kinds</a>, answer to question on MathOverflow, 2026.
%F A397400 (-1)^n * Sum_{j=1..n+1} Stirling1(m+k+j, m+k+1) * Stirling2(n+m+1, m+j) = Sum_{j=0..min(n, k)} k^(n-j) * binomial(n+m+k-j, m+k) * Stirling1(k, k-j) for m >= 0.
%F A397400 From _Peter Luschny_, Jun 24 2026: (Start)
%F A397400 A(n, k) = k^(n - k) * Sum_{j=0..k} Stirling1(k, j)*binomial(n+j, k) * k^j.
%F A397400 A(n, k) = k^(n - k) * A397420(n, k).
%F A397400 A(n, n) = A397324(n).  (End)
%e A397400 Array starts:
%e A397400   [0] 1, 1,    1,      1,       1,        1,        1,         1, ... [A000012]
%e A397400   [1] 0, 2,    5,      9,      14,       20,       27,        35, ... [A000096]
%e A397400   [2] 0, 3,   18,     56,     131,      260,      463,       763, ...
